{
  "stem": "27340.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There seemed to be a considerable amount of majority voting for this sort of thing, cross party thing.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And do you realize that by December of that same year, just six or seven weeks after the appeal was made in the House of Commons, the first train loads of children actually rolled into this country?",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, we got to remember that Britain was the only country that did something of this nature.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the original intention of saving something like 50,000 children, uh, was never reached.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think they saved something like about 11 or 12,000 children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they came over here on this famous Kindertransport.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Uh, fortunately, my brother and I were amongst those 10 or 12,000 who, in fact, were saved that way.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my parents became aware of this, and of course, signed onto this straightaway.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were fortunate enough, with a little bit of help, perhaps financial help, or guarantee as it were, a financial guarantee from an uncle of mine who had married my mother's sister.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this uncle was an English-born Jew, had, in fact, uh, guaranteed financial security so that we would not be a burden to the state.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we were integrated into this Kindertransport movement.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Kindertransport itself, I, I, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "W-we were notified when we'd have to leave.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were very, very strict rules and regulations on this.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Nazis raised no objections, provided we had not any specific debts to the state, but as children, obviously, who were not due to income tax or anything of this nature.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So from that point of view, I should imagine there was no problem there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they stipulated that we could only take as much as we could carry ourselves.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
